-- Spanish Stocks: Guipuzcoano, Sabadell, Banco Popular, Repsol Are Active
-- Paul Tobin
-- 2010-06-28T16:01:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/spanish-stocks-guipuzcoano-sabadell-banco-popular-repsol-are-active.html

          
          
             Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  rose 153.5, or
1.6 percent, to 9,688.5 in Madrid, after falling for the four
previous sessions.  
 The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market today.  
 Banco Guipuzcoano  SA (GUI SM) fell for a fifth day, losing
4.1 percent to 4.70 euros. The lender’s board agreed to be taken
over by rival  Banco Sabadell SA  (SAB SM). Sabadell offered five
ordinary shares plus five mandatory convertible three-year notes
for every eight ordinary shares of Guipuzcoano. Sabadell shares
advanced 2.8 percent to 3.74 euros.  
 Banco Popular Espanol SA  (POP SM) rose for the first time
in six days, advancing 1.9 percent to 4.46 euros. Credit Mutuel
agreed to build a 5 percent stake in Popular as the French and
Spanish lenders set up a joint venture to find new opportunities
in Spain.  
 Ferrovial SA  (FER SM) rose 3.3 percent to 5.62 euros,
ending a four-day decline. The company’s Amey Plc completed the
sale of its 66.7 percent stake in Tube Lines Limited.  
 Repsol YPF SA  (REP SM) rose for the first time in five
days, gaining 2.6 percent to 17.34 euros, after BofA Merrill
Lynch Global Research raised its recommendation on Spain’s
largest oil company to “buy.”  
